name: Plan B
overview: Plan B offers clients the chance to travel back in time to change the past, but each alteration has unintended consequences, revealing the complexity and limitations of personal agency.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: An ambitious young lawyer discovers a way to travel through time to fix his relationships and create his perfect life, but even when he knows what's going to happen next, he can't control everything.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: After Montreal police officer Mia Coleman and her partner Tyler take a lenient approach to a marital dispute, the husband, Paul Whitman, murders his wife Keri and their two small children, then kills himself. But Mia has stumbled across Plan B and finds herself able to book a trip into the past, and perhaps alter the outcome.

tagline: Reject the future. Rewrite the past.

episodes.name: Episode 1

episodes.name: Episode 2

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: Philip finds himself resentful about what he knows is about to happen in the future.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: Despite Evelyn's obvious love for him, Philip can't shake his jealousy.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: This time Philip's sure he has the perfect Plan B to make his dreams come true.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: When Philip's perfect world is hit hard by reality, he decides on a very different plan B.

1.name: Season 1

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: Police officer Mia Coleman is haunted by a case involving a murder-suicide. She calls the Plan B agency, determined to go back in time and prevent the tragedy.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: Traveling back in time to prevent a murder-suicide, Mia kidnaps the would-be killer, but her plan backfires, leaving blood on her own hands in her pursuit of justice.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: Suspended from duty, Mia's determination to prevent a sexual assault leads her down a path of vigilante justice, blurring the lines between her police work and her personal vendetta.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: Mia travels farther back in time to protect Keri from her abusive husband, forcing Mia into proximity with her own ex-boyfriend Bryson and confronting her with the complexities of their relationship.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: Mia seeks therapy to address her controlling behaviour. Paul attends counseling while Mia supervises his visits with his daughters. Mia's unresolved issues resurface, leading to a family confrontation.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: Paul attempts to reconcile with Keri, but his anger resurfaces. While Mia confronts her own demons and makes a change, Paul seeks redemption.
